.START 

Big O Tires Inc. agreed to sell about two million shares, or an 11.4% stake, to General Tire Inc. for $3 a share, as part of a supply contract. 

Big O, a tire distributor and franchiser of tire stores, said it signed a 15-year supply agreement calling for General Tire to provide it with private label and brand-name tires for its Big O retail outlets. 

Further, terms of the transaction call for General Tire to receive warrants to buy additional Big O shares, which could increase General Tire's stake to 31%. 

General Tire is owned by Continental Gummi-Werke AG of West Germany. 

In nation over-the-counter trading yesterday, Big O shares closed at $2, up 6.25 cents.
The company will have about 17.6 million shares outstanding after the transaction. 

